h4. Steps to Reproduce:
# Create a text custom field
# Configure the custom field to one issue type only(eg. Bug)
# Create 2 issues. One with Bug and one with Improvement.
# Go to the issue navigator and search in one of following JQL:
{code}
issuetype in (Bug, Improvement)
{code}
{code}
issuetype in standardIssueTypes()
{code}
# Add the custom field into the search column

h4. Expected Behaviour:
The custom field column is not showing due to the behaviour mentioned in [documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Customizing+your+Issue+Navigator]:
{quote}
Some custom fields, even if selected, do not appear in the Issue Navigator for all issues. For example, project-specific custom fields will be shown only if the filter has been restricted to that project only. Issue type custom fields will only appear if the filter has been restricted to that issue type.
{quote}

h4. Actual Behaviour:
The custom field column are showing in the issue navigator.

