When adding 'Assign to Current User' post-function to the Create Issue Transition of a workflow, it is expected to re-position the new post-function to come before 'create the issue originally' post-function, otherwise the added post-function will have no effect as described in [this Knowledge-base Article|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/Assign+to+Current+User+postfunction+doesn%27t+work+on+the+Create+transition]..

However, by default the new post-function is initially wrongly added underneath the 'Create the issue originally' post-function automatically, and many users may not know to relocate the newly added post-function, and then wonder why it's not taking effect.

To avoid this error and the confusion it causes, can it be made possible such that the newly added post-function is automatically added to the correct position with respect to the default post-functions in the transition?

